d Target]]'' (2010)\n| ''[[Wild Target (1993 film)|Cible \u00e9mouvante]]'' (1993)\n| \n|-\n| ''[[Willie & Phil]]'' (1980)\n| ''[[Jules et Jim]]'' (1962)\n| The novel ''Jules and Jim'' ([[Henri-Pierre Roch\u00e9]])\n|-\n| ''[[A Window in London]]'' (1940)\n| ''[[Metropolitan (1939 film)|Metropolitan]]'' (1939)\n| \n|-\n| ''[[The Woman I Love]]'' (1937)\n| ''L'\u00c9quipage'' (1935)\n| The novel ''L'\u00c9quipage'' ([[Joseph Kessel]])\n|-\n| ''[[The Woman in Red (1984 film)|The Woman in Red]]'' (1984)\n| ''[[Un \u00e9l\u00e9phant \u00e7a trompe \u00e9norm\u00e9ment]]'' (1976)\n| \n|}\n\n== German ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! English-language film\n! German-language film\n! Common source material (if any)\n|-\n| ''[[24 Hours of a Woman's Life]]'' (1952)\n| ''[[24 Hours in the Life of a Woman (1931 film)|24 Hours in the Life of a Woman]]'' (1931)\n| The novella ''[[Twenty-Four Hours in the Life of a Woman]]'' ([[Stefan Zweig]])\n|-\n| ''Addio Mim\u00ed!'' (1949)\n| ''[[The Charm of La Boheme]]'' (1937, Austria)\n| A modernized version of the opera ''[[La boh\u00e8me]]'' ([[Giacomo Puccini]], [[Luigi Illica]], [[Giuseppe Giacosa]], [[Henri Murger]])\n|-\n| ''[[Adorable (film)|Adorable]]'' (1933)\n| ''[[Her Grace Commands]]'' (1931)\n|\n|-\n| ''[[After the Ball (1932 film)|After the Ball]]'' (1932)\n| ''[[The Opera Ball (1931 film)|The Opera Ball]]'' (1931)\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Alone in Berlin (film)|Alone in Berlin]]'' (2016)\n| ''[[Everyone Dies Alone]]'' (1976, West Germany)\n| The novel ''[[Every Man Dies Alone]]'' ([[Hans Fallada]])\n|-\n| ''[[The Angel with the Trumpet (1950 film)|The Angel with the Trumpet]]'' (1950)\n| ''[[The Angel with the Trumpet (1948 film)|The Angel with the Trumpet]]'' (1948, Austria)\n| The novel ''Der Engel mit der Posaune'' ([[Ernst Lothar]])\n|-\n| ''[[Bachelor Mother]]'' (1939)\n| ''[[Little Mother (1935 film)|Little Mother]]'' (1935, Austria)\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Ball at Savoy (1936 film)|Ball at Savoy]]'' (1936)\n| ''Ball im Savoy'' (1935, Austria)\n| The operetta ''[[Ball im Savoy]]'' ([[Paul Abraham]], [[Alfred Gr\u00fcnwald (librettist)|Alfred Gr\u00fcnwald]], [[Fritz L\u00f6hner-Beda]])\n|-\n| ''[[Beauty and the Boss]]'' (1932)\n| ''[[Poor as a Church Mouse]]'' (1931)\n| The play ''A templom eg\u00e9re'' ([[Ladislas Fodor]])\n|-\n| ''[[Between Us Girls]]'' (1942)\n| ''[[A Precocious Girl]]'' (1934, Austria)\n| The play ''Le Fruit Vert'' (Jacques Th\u00e9ry, Regis Gignoux)\n|-\n| ''[[The Blue Angel (1959 film)|The Blue Angel]]'' (1959)\n| ''[[The Blue Angel]]'' (1930)\n| The novel ''[[Professor Unrat]]'' ([[Heinrich Mann]])\n|-\n| ''[[Bundle of Joy]]'' (1956)\n| ''[[Little Mother (1935 film)|Little Mother]]'' (1935, Austria)\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Burning Secret]]'' (1988)\n| ''[[The Burning Secret]]'' (1933)\n| The short story ''Brennendes Geheimnis'' ([[Stefan Zweig]])\n|-\n| ''[[The Captain from K\u00f6penick (1945 film)|The Captain from K\u00f6penick]]'' (1945)\n| ''[[The Captain from K\u00f6penick (1931 film)|The Captain from K\u00f6penick]]'' (1931)\n| The play ''Der Hauptmann von K\u00f6penick'' ([[Carl Zuckmayer]]), based on [[Wilhelm Voigt]]\n|-\n| ''[[The Challenge (1938 film)|The Challenge]]'' (1938)\n| ''[[Struggle for the Matterhorn]]'' (1928, Switzerland)\n| \n|-\n| ''[[The Church Mouse]]'' (1934)\n| ''[[Poor as a Church Mouse]]'' (1931)\n| The play ''A templom eg\u00e9re'' ([[Ladislas Fodor]])\n|-\n| ''[[City of Angels (film)|City of Angels]]'' (1998)\n| ''[[Wings of Desire|Der Himmel \u00fcber Berlin]]'' (1987, West Germany)\n| \n|-\n| ''[[Confession (1937 film)|Confession]]'' (1937)\n| ''[[Mazurka (film)|Mazurka]]'' (1935)\n|\n|-\n| ''[[The Countess of Monte Cristo (1934 film)|The Countess of Monte Cristo]]'' (1934)\n| ''[[The Countess of Monte Cristo (1932 film)|The Countess of Monte Cristo]]'' (1932)\n|\n|-\n| ''[[The Countess of Monte Cristo (1948 film)|The Countess of Monte Cristo]]'' (1948)\n| ''[[The Countess of Monte Cristo (1932 film)|The Countess of Monte Cristo]]'' (1932)\n|\n|-\n| 