{"title_page": "Navigator Records", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2017}}\n{{Use British English|date=August 2015}}\n{{infobox record label\n| image = [[File:Navigator_Records_logo.png]]\n| parent = \n| founded = 2008\n| founder = \n| distributor = [[Proper Music Distribution]]\n| genre = [[folk music|Folk]] and roots music. \n| country = United Kingdom\n| location      = London\n| url = {{unbulleted list|[http://www.navigatorrecords.co.uk/ Navigator Records]}}\n}}\n\n'''Navigator Records''' is a small [[independent record label]] in the United Kingdom, specialising in [[folk music|folk]] and roots music. It is wholly owned by [[Proper Music Distribution]]<ref name= \"DueDil\">{{cite web | url=https://www.duedil.com/company/06394939/navigator-records-limited/people | title=Navigator Records Limited|publisher= DueDil|accessdate =25 April 2014}}</ref> and was launched in 2008.\n\nMusicians who have recorded on Navigator Records include  [[Alyth (singer)|Alyth]],<ref name=\"List\">{{cite magazine | url=http://www.list.co.uk/articles/navigator-records/ | title=Aylth \u2013 People Like Me |magazine=[[The List (magazine)|The List]] | date=2 April 2009 | accessdate=30 June 2013}}</ref> [[Jon Boden]],<ref name=\"Boden\">{{cite web | url=http://www.navigatorrecords.co.uk/artists/jon-boden/ | title=Jon Boden | publisher=Navigator Records | accessdate=10 April 2013}}</ref> [[Bellowhead]],<ref name=\"Green\">{{cite news | url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/music/worldfolkandjazz/9725048/Bellowhead-interview-Rebooting-folk-for-the-Top-20-or-for-a-packed-pub-at-2am.html | title=Bellowhead interview: Rebooting folk for the Top 20 \u2013 or for a packed pub at 2am | work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] | date=6 December 2012 | accessdate=27 March 2013 | author=Green, Thomas H | location=London}}</ref> [[Bella Hardy]],<ref name=\"Coleman\">{{cite news | url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/reviews/album-bella-hardy-songs-lost-amp-stolen-navigator-2269156.html | title=Album: Bella Hardy, Songs Lost & Stolen (Navigator) | work=[[The Independent]] | date=17 April 2011 | accessdate=25 April 2014 | author=[[Nick Coleman (British writer)|Coleman, Nick]] | location=London}}</ref> [[Boo Hewerdine]],<ref name=\"Fish\">{{cite web | url=http://www.fishrecords.co.uk/artists/godblesstheprettythings.html | title=Boo Hewerdine: God Bless the Pretty Things | publisher=Fish Records | accessdate=27 March 2013}}</ref> [[Benji Kirkpatrick]],<ref name=\"Kirkpatrick\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.discogs.com/artist/1228990-Benji-Kirkpatrick |title=Benji Kirkpatrick |website=[[Discogs]] |access-date=17 April 2020}}</ref> [[Sean Lakeman]],<ref name=\"Gill\">{{cite news | url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/reviews/album-kathryn-roberts--sean-lakeman-hidden-people-navigator-7917503.html | title=Album: Kathryn Roberts & Sean Lakeman, Hidden People (Navigator) | work=[[The Independent]] | date=7 July 2012 | accessdate=9 April 2013 | author=Gill, Andy | location=London}}</ref>  [[Lau (band)|Lau]],<ref name=\"Lau\">{{cite web | url=http://www.worldmusic.co.uk/lau_arc_light | title=Lau \u2013 \"Arc Light\" | publisher=Worldmusic.co.uk | accessdate=27 March 2013}}</ref> [[Merrymouth (band)|Merrymouth]],<ref name=\"Merrymouth\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.discogs.com/artist/3848332-Merrymouth |title=Merrymouth |website=[[Discogs]] |access-date=17 April 2020}}</ref> [[Oysterband]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.folkradio.co.uk/2013/11/new-album-oysterband-diamonds-on-the-water/ |title=Oysterband annunce new album \u2013 Diamonds on the Water |last=Gallacher |first=Alex |date=22 November 2013 |website=[[Folk Radio UK]] |access-date=17 April 2020}}</ref> [[Paper Aeroplanes]],<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.navigatorrecords.co.uk/artists/paper-aeroplanes/ | title=Paper Aeroplanes \u2013 Little Letters Countdown | publisher=Navigator Records | date=7 May 2013 | accessdate=22 May 2013}}</ref>\n[[Kathryn Roberts]] and [[Lucy Ward (musician)|Lucy Ward]].<ref name=\"Artists\">{{cite web | url=http://www.navigatorrecords.co.uk/artists/ | title=Artists | publisher=Navigator Records | accessdate=27 March 2013}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.navigatorrecords.co.uk/  Official website]\n\n[[Category:2008 establishments in England]]\n[[Category:British independent record labels]]\n[[Category:Folk record labels]]\n[[Category:Record labels established in 2008]]\n[[Category:Record labels from London]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2017}}\n{{Use British English|date=August 2015}}\n{{infobox record label\n| image = [[File:Navigator_Records_logo.png]]\n| parent = \n| founded = 2008\n| founder = \n| distributor = [[Proper Music Distribution]]\n| genre = [[folk music|Folk]] and roots music. \n| country = United Kingdom\n| location      = London\n| url = {{unbulleted list|[http://www.navigatorrecords.co.uk/ Navigator Records]}}\n}}\n\n'''Navigator Records''' is a small [[independent record label]] in the United Kingdom, specialising in [[folk music|folk]] and roots music. It is wholly owned by [[Proper Music Distribution]]<ref name= \"DueDil\">{{cite web | url=https://www.duedil.com/company/06394939/navigator-records-limited/people | title=Navigator Records Limited|publisher= DueDil|accessdate =25 April 2014}}</ref> and was launched in 2008.\n\nMusicians who have recorded on Navigator Records include  [[Alyth (singer)|Alyth]],<ref name=\"List\">{{cite magazine | url=http://www.list.co.uk/articles/navigator-records/ | title=Aylth \u2013 People Like Me |magazine=[[The List (magazine)|The List]] | date=2 April 2009 | accessdate=30 June 2013}}</ref> [[Jon Boden]],<ref name=\"Boden\">{{cite web | url=http://www.navigatorrecords.co.uk/artists/jon-boden/ | title=Jon Boden | publisher=Navigator Records | accessdate=10 April 2013}}</ref> [[Bellowhead]],<ref name=\"Green\">{{cite news | url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/music/worldfolkandjazz/9725048/Bellowhea